solution: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.horsepower ASC LIMIT 1;
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId ORDER BY T1.Horsepower LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.horsepower ASC LIMIT 1;
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId ORDER BY T1.Horsepower LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Weight < ( SELECT AVG(Weight) FROM cars_data )

solution: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)
answer: SELECT T1.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Weight < ( SELECT AVG(Weight) FROM cars_data )

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';
answer: SELECT T2.Maker FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Year = 1970;

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';
answer: SELECT T2.Maker FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Year = 1970 GROUP BY T2.Maker

solution: SELECT T2.Make ,  T1.Year FROM CARS_DATA AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Year  =  (SELECT min(YEAR) FROM CARS_DATA);
answer: SELECT T2.Make, MIN(T1.Year) FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId GROUP BY T2.Make

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.model FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Model  =  T2.Model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T3 ON T2.MakeId  =  T3.Id JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T4 ON T1.Maker  =  T4.Id WHERE T3.weight  <  3500 AND T4.FullName != 'Ford Motor Company';
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Weight < 3500 AND T2.Maker NOT IN ( SELECT Maker FROM car_makers WHERE FullName = 'Ford Motor Company' )

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.model FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Model  =  T2.Model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T3 ON T2.MakeId  =  T3.Id JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T4 ON T1.Maker  =  T4.Id WHERE T3.weight  <  3500 AND T4.FullName != 'Ford Motor Company';

solution: SELECT CountryName FROM countries EXCEPT SELECT T1.CountryName FROM countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.countryId  =  T2.Country;
answer: SELECT T2.Country FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN countries AS T2 ON T1.Country = T2.CountryId GROUP BY T2.Country HAVING COUNT(T1.Id) = 0

solution: SELECT CountryName FROM countries EXCEPT SELECT T1.CountryName FROM countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.countryId  =  T2.Country;
answer: SELECT T2.Country FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN countries AS T2 ON T1.Country = T2.CountryId WHERE T1.Maker IS NULL

solution: select t1.id ,  t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id  =  t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*)  >=  2 intersect select t1.id ,  t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id  =  t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model  =  t3.model group by t1.id having count(*)  >  3;
answer: SELECT T1.Maker, T2.Id FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN model_list AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.Maker GROUP BY T2.Maker HAVING COUNT(T2.Model) >= 2 AND COUNT(DISTINCT T1.Id) > 3

solution: SELECT T1.Id ,  T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING count(*)  >=  2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.Id ,  T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING count(*)  >  3;
answer: SELECT T1.Id, T2.Maker FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN model_list AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.Maker GROUP BY T2.Maker HAVING COUNT(T2.Model) >= 2 AND SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Model IN ( SELECT Model FROM model_list GROUP BY Model ORDER BY COUNT(Model) DESC LIMIT 3 ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 3

solution: SELECT T1.countryId ,  T1.CountryName FROM Countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country GROUP BY T1.countryId HAVING count(*)  >  3 UNION SELECT T1.countryId ,  T1.CountryName FROM Countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T3 ON T2.Id  =  T3.Maker WHERE T3.Model  =  'fiat';
answer: SELECT T1.Id, T1.Country FROM countries AS T1 INNER JOIN car_makers AS T2 ON T1.CountryId = T2.Country WHERE T2.Maker IN ( SELECT Maker FROM model_list GROUP BY Maker HAVING COUNT(Model) > 3 ) OR T2.Model = 'fiat'

solution: select t1.countryid ,  t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*)  >  3 union select t1.countryid ,  t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id  =  t3.maker where t3.model  =  'fiat';
answer: SELECT T1.CountryId, T1.CountryName FROM countries AS T1 INNER JOIN car_makers AS T2 ON T1.CountryId = T2.Country WHERE T2.Maker IN ( SELECT Maker FROM model_list GROUP BY Maker HAVING COUNT(Maker) > 3 ) OR T2.Maker = 'Fiat'

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72
answer: SELECT T1.Continent, AVG(T2.LifeExpectancy), SUM(T2.Population) FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.Code WHERE T2.LifeExpectancy < 72 GROUP BY T1.Continent;

solution: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72
